---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Rhumb's privacy policy. What we collect, what we don't, and how we handle your data."
  canonical="/privacy"
>
  <div class="bg-navy min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-14 pb-24">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <span class="text-xs font-mono font-semibold text-amber uppercase tracking-widest">
          Legal
        </span>
        <h1 class="font-display font-bold text-3xl text-slate-100 leading-tight tracking-tight mt-4 mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 font-mono">
          Last updated: March 11, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Overview
          </h2>
          <p>
            Rhumb (operated by Supertrained LLC) is a developer tool that
            scores APIs for AI agent compatibility. We are committed to
            transparency about what we collect and why.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            <strong class="text-slate-200">
              The short version: we collect minimal data, we don&#39;t
              sell any of it, and we don&#39;t track you across sites.
            </strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            What we collect
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                API query logs:
              </strong>{" "}
              When you use our API or MCP server, we log search terms and
              timestamps to improve relevance. These logs do not contain
              personally identifiable information (PII).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Web analytics:
              </strong>{" "}
              We use Google Analytics 4 and Microsoft Clarity for
              anonymized usage analytics. These tools collect standard
              web metrics (page views, session duration, device type).
              Both are configured with IP anonymization enabled.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Error logs:
              </strong>{" "}
              Server error logs may contain request metadata (URL, HTTP
              method, status code) for debugging. These are retained for
              30 days and contain no PII.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            What we do NOT collect
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; We do not collect personal information (names, emails,
              addresses)
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We do not collect payment information or authentication
              tokens
            </li>
            <li>&bull; We do not use cookies for tracking or advertising</li>
            <li>&bull; We do not track you across other websites</li>
            <li>
              &bull; We do not build user profiles or sell data to third
              parties
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; We do not use your API queries to train machine learning
              models
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            How we use your data
          </h2>
          <p>Data collected is used solely to:</p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; Improve search relevance and service coverage</li>
            <li>&bull; Monitor API performance and uptime</li>
            <li>
              &bull; Understand aggregate usage patterns (which categories are
              most searched, which services are most viewed)
            </li>
            <li>&bull; Debug errors and improve reliability</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Third-party services
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3 mt-3">
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Google Analytics 4
              </strong>{" "}
              — anonymized web analytics.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Google Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">
                Microsoft Clarity
              </strong>{" "}
              — session recordings and heatmaps (anonymized).{" "}
              <a
                href="https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-us/privacystatement"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Microsoft Privacy Statement
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Vercel</strong> —
              hosting.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Vercel Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Supabase</strong> —
              database hosting.{" "}
              <a
                href="https://supabase.com/privacy"
                class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
              >
                Supabase Privacy Policy
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Your rights (GDPR / CCPA)
          </h2>
          <p>
            Since we collect minimal, anonymized data, most rights
            (access, deletion, portability) apply to very limited data.
            However, you have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Access</strong> —
              request a copy of any data associated with your usage
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Deletion</strong> —
              request deletion of any stored data
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull; <strong class="text-slate-200">Opt-out</strong> —
              disable analytics by using a browser ad blocker or
              do-not-track setting
            </li>
            <li>
              &bull;{" "}
              <strong class="text-slate-200">Data portability</strong>{" "}
              — request your data in a machine-readable format
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-3">
            For any privacy-related requests, contact{" "}
            <a
              href="mailto:privacy@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              privacy@supertrained.ai
            </a>
            .
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Data retention
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
            <li>&bull; API query logs: retained for 90 days</li>
            <li>&bull; Error logs: retained for 30 days</li>
            <li>
              &bull; Web analytics: per Google Analytics and Microsoft Clarity
              default retention policies
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Changes to this policy
          </h2>
          <p>
            We will update this page when our data practices change. For
            significant changes, we&#39;ll note the update in our{" "}
            <a
              href="/changelog"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              changelog
            </a>
            .
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl text-slate-100 mb-3">
            Contact
          </h2>
          <p>
            For privacy-related questions or requests:
            <br />
            <a
              href="mailto:privacy@supertrained.ai"
              class="text-amber hover:underline underline-offset-2"
            >
              privacy@supertrained.ai
            </a>
          </p>
          <p class="mt-3">
            Supertrained LLC
            <br />
            Los Angeles, CA
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
